{"id":20,"date":"2016-07-07T16:13:57","date_gmt":"2016-07-07T15:13:57","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/about-us\/parents-association\/"},"modified":"2022-09-15T10:41:46","modified_gmt":"2022-09-15T09:41:46","slug":"parents-association","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.beechwood.org.uk\/about-us\/parents-association\/","title":{"rendered":"Beechwood Parents Association"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>The Beechwood PA provide an\u00a0active and enthusiastic support for the school, arranging several fund-raising and social events each year.<\/p>\n<p>Not only this the Beechwood PA also acts as an important channel of communication by providing a class representative for every class in the school. These representatives can bring any concerns, queries or opinions of parents to regular meetings with the Headteacher.<\/p>\n<h3>PA Contact Details<\/h3>\n<p>Please feel free to contact us at any time: Dan Jude, Chair,<a href=\"mailto:Daniel_Jude@hotmail.co.uk\"> <\/a> Daniel_Jude@hotmail.co.uk<\/p>\n<h3>PA Meetings<\/h3>\n<p>Most PA meetings for this academic year will be held at 8pm in the Old Chapel but with a Zoom access option.\u00a0 Drinks and nibbles will be served from 7.30pm.\u00a0Dates will be published in the School Diary sent at the start of each term to parents, but some may be added or altered depending on parent availability. Parents\/Guardians will be contacted via Parentmail about meeting dates.<\/p>\n<h3>Committee and Class Reps<\/h3>\n<p>All parents of pupils in the school are automatically members of the Beechwood PA, a subscription being charged with each termly account. At the Annual General Meeting of the Association a committee is elected from which a Chairman, Vice-Chairman, Treasurer and Secretary are chosen. The school is always interested to hear from parents that wish to contribute in any way possible. Even if it is for one event, or a couple of meetings each year, your contributions are warmly welcomed.<\/p>\n\